        prd_ref="PRD-EMPLOYER-CONTACT-001"
        llm_profile="anthropic-opus"
        acceptance="TS covers: module design, API contracts, data model changes, file-by-file implementation plan, test strategy, acceptance criteria mapping"
        prompt="PLANNER PHASE: Write a Technical Spec at /Users/theb/Documents/Windsurf/cobuilder-harness/docs/sds/employer-contact-search/SD-EMPLOYER-CONTACT-E1.md. MANDATORY: Invoke Skill('dspy-development'). Use the BS and both research evidence files. CRITICAL: Follow Clean Architecture (feature-first) from BS Section 13 and docs/AGENCHECK_CLEANUP.md. The employer_research/ directory must have: domain.py (models, no I/O), classifier.py (pure logic), service.py (orchestration), repository.py (Supabase adapter), researcher.py (DSPy/Perplexity/web search adapter), router.py (entrypoint). Dependencies flow inward: entrypoints → service_layer → domain ← adapters. The TS must include: (1) DSPy Module design: EmployerContactResearcher(dspy.Module) in researcher.py with Signatures for search, classify, score, deduplicate. (2) Dual-source research: Perplexity Deep Research API + web search (Brave/Google). NOT Perplexity alone. (3) Data model: employer_contacts table (BS Section 7.1), Supabase in repository.py. (4) Classification + scoring in domain layer (no API deps). (5) File-by-file plan matching the feature-first structure. (6) Test strategy per layer. (7) BS Section 5 acceptance criteria mapped to tests."
    ];

    // ── Planner gate: Guardian reviews TS quality ──
    gate_planner [
